    <p class="section-number">02 · Diagnostic sequence on a leak call</p>
    <h2>Five-step process.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Visual inspection of leak location.</strong> Inside the cabinet vs outside vs in front vs behind tells us a lot before we start tools.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost drain line check.</strong> Visual access to the drain port plus probe test. If clogged, this is the answer.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket and condensation pattern check.</strong> Especially if interior pool plus visible cabinet condensation.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain pan and condensate pump operation (if applicable to the install).</strong> Listen for pump cycling, check for pan overflow.</li>
      <li><strong>Tank/sump check (only if 1-4 ruled out).</strong> Last because it's the rarest and most invasive.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

